HEADWORD: Chelerythrine
<hw>Chel`e*ryth"rine</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/
celandine + <grk>'eryqro`s</grk> red.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An
alkaloidal principle obtained from the celandine, and named from the red
color of its salts. It is a colorless crystalline substance, and acts as
an acrid narcotic poison. It is identical with
<altname>sanguinarine</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

